"Pagbigyan" explores the feeling of burnout from love, capturing the sense of defeat when a relationship feels beyond saving. The song portrays the realistic side of love, acknowledging that it isn't always perfect and can be painful and unforgiving. 

Performed by: Sugarcane
Written by: Carl Angelo D. Guerzon, Francis Luis D. Beato
